---
import CaseStudyLayout from "../../layouts/CaseStudyLayout.astro";
import { ArrowLeft, ArrowRight, XCircle, Clock, Zap } from "@lucide/astro";
import ekaLogo from "../../public/assets/eka-logo.svg";
---

<CaseStudyLayout
    title="Case Study: High-Velocity Web Infrastructure | Kunal Katre"
>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <div slot="hero" class="not-prose mb-12 animate-fade-in w-full">
        <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-12 items-center">
            <div class="flex-1 space-y-6">
                <a
                    href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL + "/#work"}
                    class="btn btn-ghost btn-sm gap-2 pl-0 hover:bg-transparent hover:text-primary transition-colors duration-300"
                >
                    <ArrowLeft />
                    Back to Work
                </a>

                <div
                    class="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm font-medium text-base-content/70"
                >
                    <span>Project for</span>
                    <img
                        src={ekaLogo.src}
                        alt="Eka Care logo"
                        class="h-6 w-auto"
                    />
                </div>

                <h1
                    class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-serif font-bold leading-tight"
                >
                    From Bottleneck to Self-Serve
                </h1>

                <p
                    class="text-xl text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl"
                >
                    I architected a Decentralized Publishing Engine that
                    transformed our website from an "Engineering Ticket" to a
                    "Design-Led Operation," reducing campaign TAT by 80% and
                    giving Marketing 100% autonomy.
                </p>

                <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 pt-4">
                    <div
                        class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 backdrop-blur-sm"
                    >
                        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary">80%</div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
                            TAT Reduction
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 backdrop-blur-sm"
                    >
                        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-secondary">90+</div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
                            Lighthouse Score
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 backdrop-blur-sm"
                    >
                        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent">200+</div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
                            Engineering Hours Saved
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div
                class="flex-1 w-full max-w-md lg:max-w-full flex justify-center"
            >
                <div class="mockup-browser border-primary">
                    <div class="mockup-browser-toolbar">
                        <div class="input">https://eka.care</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-base-200 flex justify-center px-4 py-16">
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">
                                Web Infrastructure
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-base-content/70">
                                High-Velocity Publishing Engine
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="space-y-16">
        <!-- Section 1 -->
        <section id="setup">
            <h2>1. The Executive Summary: From Bottleneck to Self-Serve</h2>
            <p>
                In a hyper-growth startup, Marketing needs to move at the speed
                of culture, but Engineering is often locked in product sprints.
                At Eka Care, our web presence was stifled by this
                dependency—simple copy changes took days, and new campaign pages
                took weeks.
            </p>

            <div
                class="alert shadow-lg bg-base-200/80 border-l-4 border-primary not-prose my-8"
            >
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">The Core Innovation</h3>
                    <p class="text-base-content/80">
                        I didn't just "redesign the website"; I architected a <strong
                            >Decentralized Publishing Engine</strong
                        >. By migrating to Webflow and integrating an
                        AI-assisted development workflow, I shifted the website
                        from an "Engineering Ticket" to a "Design-Led
                        Operation," reducing campaign Turnaround Time (TAT) by <strong
                            >80%</strong
                        > and giving Marketing 100% autonomy.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>The Challenge: The "Engineering Wall"</h3>
            <p>
                The existing website was a hard-coded React app. While
                performant, it was operationally broken for a marketing team:
            </p>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-8">
                <div class="card bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div
                            class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-error/10 text-error flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
                        >
                            <XCircle />
                        </div>
                        <h4 class="card-title text-base mb-2">Zero Autonomy</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm italic text-base-content/80">
                            Marketing couldn't fix a typo without a developer
                            PR.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div
                            class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-warning/10 text-warning flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
                        >
                            <Clock />
                        </div>
                        <h4 class="card-title text-base mb-2">
                            Slow-to-Market
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-sm italic text-base-content/80">
                            Launching a "Hackathon" landing page required
                            pulling engineers off core product work.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div
                            class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-info/10 text-info flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
                        >
                            <Zap />
                        </div>
                        <h4 class="card-title text-base mb-2">
                            The "Bandwidth" Trap
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-sm italic text-base-content/80">
                            As the sole designer, I risked becoming the new
                            bottleneck—replacing "waiting for devs" with
                            "waiting for design."
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div
                class="alert shadow-lg bg-success/10 border-l-4 border-success not-prose my-8"
            >
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">The Goal</h3>
                    <p class="text-base-content/80">
                        <strong
                            >Build a system that allows high-fidelity design <em
                                >and</em
                            > instant publishing, without requiring a single hour
                            of core engineering time.</strong
                        >
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 2 -->
        <section id="strategy">
            <h2>2. The Strategy: Operationalizing "No-Code"</h2>
            <p>
                I treated the website as a product, not a brochure. My strategy
                focused on three operational pillars:
            </p>

            <div class="space-y-8 my-8">
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div
                            class="text-6xl font-serif text-primary/20 absolute top-4 right-4"
                        >
                            A
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="card-title text-xl mb-2 relative z-10">
                            The "Pixel-to-Publish" Migration (Webflow)
                        </h3>
                        <p class="relative z-10 text-base-content/80 mb-4">
                            I collaborated with the Brand Team to translate
                            their new visual identity into a production-grade
                            Webflow system.
                        </p>

                        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                            <div
                                class="stat bg-success/10 border border-success/20 rounded-lg"
                            >
                                <div class="stat-title">Outcome</div>
                                <div class="stat-value text-success">
                                    1 Week
                                </div>
                                <div class="stat-desc">
                                    15+ page site overhaul
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div
                                class="stat bg-info/10 border border-info/20 rounded-lg"
                            >
                                <div class="stat-title">The "Secret Sauce"</div>
                                <div class="stat-value text-info text-sm">
                                    Client-First
                                </div>
                                <div class="stat-desc">
                                    Strict class-naming convention
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div
                            class="text-6xl font-serif text-secondary/20 absolute top-4 right-4"
                        >
                            B
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="card-title text-xl mb-2 relative z-10">
                            The "Self-Serve" CMS (Democratization)
                        </h3>
                        <p class="relative z-10 text-base-content/80 mb-4">
                            I identified the high-frequency requests (Blogs,
                            News, SEO tweaks) and built a robust CMS backend.
                        </p>

                        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                            <div
                                class="stat bg-secondary/10 border border-secondary/20 rounded-lg"
                            >
                                <div class="stat-title">The Handoff</div>
                                <div class="stat-value text-secondary text-sm">
                                    Training
                                </div>
                                <div class="stat-desc">
                                    Workshops for content team
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div
                                class="stat bg-success/10 border border-success/20 rounded-lg"
                            >
                                <div class="stat-title">Result</div>
                                <div class="stat-value text-success">5-10</div>
                                <div class="stat-desc">
                                    Articles/week, zero design intervention
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div
                            class="text-6xl font-serif text-accent/20 absolute top-4 right-4"
                        >
                            C
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="card-title text-xl mb-2 relative z-10">
                            The AI-Augmented Workflow (Speed)
                        </h3>
                        <p class="relative z-10 text-base-content/80 mb-4">
                            For bespoke campaign pages (like the Hackathon), I
                            couldn't rely on standard templates. I built a
                            personal "AI Ops" workflow to act as a one-person
                            dev team:
                        </p>

                        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                            <div
                                class="stat bg-accent/10 border border-accent/20 rounded-lg"
                            >
                                <div class="stat-title">Visuals</div>
                                <div class="stat-value text-accent text-sm">
                                    Napkin.ai
                                </div>
                                <div class="stat-desc">
                                    Generate infographics in minutes
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div
                                class="stat bg-info/10 border border-info/20 rounded-lg"
                            >
                                <div class="stat-title">Code</div>
                                <div class="stat-value text-info text-sm">
                                    Cursor AI
                                </div>
                                <div class="stat-desc">Custom HTML/CSS/JS</div>
                            </div>
                            <div
                                class="stat bg-success/10 border border-success/20 rounded-lg"
                            >
                                <div class="stat-title">Result</div>
                                <div class="stat-value text-success">
                                    5→1 Day
                                </div>
                                <div class="stat-desc">
                                    Custom landing page build time
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 3 -->
        <section id="highlight">
            <h2>3. Key Highlight: The "Hackathon" Campaign</h2>
            <div class="card bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 my-8">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h3 class="card-title text-xl mb-4">Context</h3>
                    <p class="text-base-content/80">
                        We needed a high-energy landing page for a developer
                        hackathon. It needed to look distinct from our corporate
                        brand—edgy, dark mode, and interactive.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 my-8">
                <div class="card bg-error/10 border border-error/20">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-error mb-4">
                            ❌ Old Process
                        </h4>
                        <div class="space-y-2">
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                                <span class="badge badge-error">Week 1</span>
                                <span>Design</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                                <span class="badge badge-error">Week 2</span>
                                <span>Development</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="divider my-4"></div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
                            <strong>Total: 2 weeks</strong> - Often missing market
                            windows
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card bg-success/10 border border-success/20">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-success mb-4">
                            ✅ New Process
                        </h4>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                                <span class="badge badge-success">Morning</span>
                                <span class="text-sm"
                                    >Brainstormed & Wireframed in Figma</span
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                                <span class="badge badge-success"
                                    >Afternoon</span
                                >
                                <span class="text-sm"
                                    >Generated assets using AI tools</span
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                                <span class="badge badge-success">Evening</span>
                                <span class="text-sm"
                                    >Built & Hosted on Webflow</span
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                                <span class="badge badge-primary"
                                    >Next Morning</span
                                >
                                <span class="text-sm font-bold">Live</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="divider my-4"></div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-success font-bold">
                            <strong>Total: 24 hours</strong> - Captured 100% of traffic
                            spike
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div
                class="alert shadow-lg bg-primary/10 border-l-4 border-primary not-prose my-8"
            >
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Impact</h3>
                    <p class="text-base-content/80">
                        We captured <strong
                            >100% of the initial traffic spike</strong
                        > because we launched <em>before</em> the buzz died down.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 4 -->
        <section id="impact">
            <h2>4. The Results: Operational Metrics</h2>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-8 not-prose">
                <div
                    class="stats shadow bg-success/10 border border-success/20 col-span-1"
                >
                    <div class="stat">
                        <div class="stat-title">Speed</div>
                        <div class="stat-value text-success">
                            1 Week → 1 Day
                        </div>
                        <div class="stat-desc">Campaign TAT reduction</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div
                    class="stats shadow bg-primary/10 border border-primary/20 col-span-1"
                >
                    <div class="stat">
                        <div class="stat-title">Performance</div>
                        <div class="stat-value text-primary">90+</div>
                        <div class="stat-desc">Lighthouse Score maintained</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div
                    class="stats shadow bg-info/10 border border-info/20 col-span-1"
                >
                    <div class="stat">
                        <div class="stat-title">Savings</div>
                        <div class="stat-value text-info">200+ Hours</div>
                        <div class="stat-desc">
                            Engineering hours saved/year
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>Reflection: The "Senior" Take</h3>
            <div class="card bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 my-8">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <blockquote
                        class="text-lg italic text-base-content/80 mb-4"
                    >
                        "This project wasn't about learning Webflow; it was
                        about <strong>Resource Allocation</strong>. By removing
                        the website from the engineering backlog, I didn't just
                        build a site—I gave the engineering team their time
                        back. I proved that with the right 'No-Code + AI' stack,
                        a design team can own the entire funnel from Figma to
                        Production."
                    </blockquote>
                    <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary">
                        — Kunal Katre, Web Principal & Design Engineer
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>Key Learnings</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Operational Thinking > Technical Mastery.</strong> The
                    biggest impact came from solving resource allocation, not just
                    technical implementation.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>No-Code Doesn't Mean No-Architecture.</strong> The Client-First
                    system I implemented ensures long-term maintainability and prevents
                    future bottlenecks.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>AI as a Design Multiplier.</strong> Using AI tools strategically
                    (not as a replacement) can compress development cycles without
                    sacrificing quality.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Self-Serve Systems Scale.</strong> Teaching the content
                    team to publish independently created sustainable operational
                    velocity.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Next Project CTA -->
        <div class="not-prose mt-24">
            <div class="divider"></div>
            <div
                class="card bg-base-200/50 hover:bg-base-200 transition-colors border border-base-300 cursor-pointer group"
            >
                <a
                    href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL + "/case-studies/heart-rate"}
                    class="card-body flex-row items-center gap-6"
                >
                    <div class="flex-1">
                        <div
                            class="text-sm font-bold opacity-60 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1"
                        >
                            Next Case Study
                        </div>
                        <h3
                            class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold group-hover:text-primary transition-colors"
                        >
                            Architecting an Engagement Engine
                        </h3>
                        <p class="mt-2 text-base-content/70">
                            See how I transformed a failing feature into a core
                            driver of user retention.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="hidden md:block">
                        <span class="btn btn-primary btn-circle">
                            <ArrowRight />
                        </span>
                    </div>
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</CaseStudyLayout>
